cat_initialMessage: First time here? Perfect, let me teach you the art of productive postponing...
cat_initialMessageForVeterans: Welcome back! Ready to procrastinate like a pro?
cat_addPageMessage: Perfect, let's pretend you're going to do all this one day...
cat_addAPage_0: Oh great, another page of future regrets...
cat_addAPage_1: Your ambition is adorable. Let's add more things to not do!
cat_addAPage_3: Making lists is basically the same as doing things, right?
cat_addAPage_4: Expanding your procrastination empire, I see...
cat_addAPage_5: Another page? You haven't even looked at the first one!
cat_addAPage_6: Ah yes, quantity over actually doing them. Smart strategy!
cat_addAPage_7: Your optimism is both inspiring and concerning...
cat_addAPage_8: Starting to think you just enjoy writing lists...
cat_addAPage_9: Look who's feeling ambitious today! *sarcastic meow*
cat_addAPage_10: Sure, why not? The more the merrier... and the later!
cat_addAPage_11: At this rate, you'll need a whole book of 'someday maybe'
cat_addAPage_12: *sigh* Fine, here's more space for your theoretical productivity
cat_addAPage_13: Adding pages won't make the tasks do themselves, you know...
cat_addAPage_14: Achievement unlocked: Master of Digital Hoarding!
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_0: Hey, I see some empty spaces just begging for procrastination...
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_1: Look! Empty tasks waiting for their turn to be ignored...
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_2: Hmm... seems like you haven't filled all your excuses yet.
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_3: Why start a new page when you can procrastinate right here?
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_4: There's still room for more unfulfilled dreams on this page!
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_5: I spy with my little eye... some perfectly good procrastination spots!
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_6: Let's not get ahead of ourselves... you still have space to disappoint me here.
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_7: Hold up! You've got some premium procrastination real estate right here.
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_8: Oh look, blank spaces! Perfect for tasks you'll definitely do *winks*
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_9: Why open a new can of procrastination when this one isn't full yet?
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_10: Trying to escape your current tasks? Nice try, but you missed some spots!
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_11: Ambitious today, aren't we? But you still have room for more delayed dreams here.
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_12: Breaking news: Empty task slots found! Film at... well, later.
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_13: Before we add more to your 'someday' list, there's space in your 'not today' list.
cat_enoughSpaceToAddPage_14: Your current page is still thirsty for more unfinished tasks...
cat_confirmAddPage: Are you sure? You already have {count} tasks awaiting your goodwill...
cat_taskCompleted_0: Congratulations! You completed a task! Now you only have... all the others left. *sarcastic applause*
cat_taskCompleted_1: Wow, you actually did something! I'm impressed. No, really, I am. This is rare.
cat_taskCompleted_2: One task down! Only 847 more to go before you feel actually productive.
cat_taskCompleted_3: Achievement unlocked: Finally Did Something! (Rarity: Legendary)
cat_taskCompleted_4: You marked it as done? What a novelty! I'll even mark it on the calendar... oh wait, that's also a task.
cat_taskCompleted_5: Congrats! You cleared a task from the list. Now it's... reorganized. So productive!
cat_taskCompleted_6: One less task! That must have been exhausting. Need a break? *winks*
cat_taskCompleted_7: Wow, did you actually do that? Or just deleted it because you were embarrassed? No judgment.
cat_taskCompleted_8: Task completed! Now you can procrastinate the others with a lighter conscience.
cat_taskCompleted_9: A victory! Small, but a victory. I'll celebrate... later.
cat_taskCompleted_10: Did you actually do that or just forgot what it was? Either way, congrats!
cat_taskCompleted_11: Task removed successfully! I hope you actually did it, not just deleted it out of laziness...
cat_taskCompleted_12: Congratulations! You completed a task. Now show me you won't add 5 new ones in its place.
cat_taskCompleted_13: One less task on the list! That must have been hard. Need a break?
cat_taskCompleted_14: Task completed! I'm proud. No wait, that's too much. I'm... mildly surprised.
cat_taskAdded_0: Another task? Sure, why not? Your 'someday' list is getting epic!
cat_taskAdded_1: Added a task! I'll note it down on my list of 'things you'll probably never do'.
cat_taskAdded_2: One more for the collection! Your list is getting as big as your capacity to procrastinate.
cat_taskAdded_3: Task added successfully! Now it can wait patiently along with all the others.
cat_taskAdded_4: Great! One more thing for you to think you'll do and then forget. Classic!
cat_taskAdded_5: Added a task? What a surprise! *not surprised*
cat_taskAdded_6: One more task on the list! Your theoretical productivity is increasing exponentially.
cat_taskAdded_7: Task registered! I'll let you know when you actually do something. Spoiler: might take a while.
cat_taskAdded_8: Added a task? Perfect! Now it can keep company with all the others you haven't done.
cat_taskAdded_9: One more for the pile! Your list is getting more impressive than your motivation.
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_0: Trying to delete a task that doesn't even exist? That's a new level of procrastination...
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_1: Congratulations! You managed to delete nothing. Achievement unlocked: Master of the Void!
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_2: You clicked 'done' on an empty task? That's like... completing the void? Deep.
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_3: Trying to finish nothing? That's as productive as procrastinating the void.
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_4: Wow, you really managed to do nothing with nothing! Impressive.
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_5: Deleting an empty task? That's like winning an award for doing nothing. Congrats!
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_6: You tried to finish... what exactly? The air? The void? Procrastination itself?
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_7: Empty task deleted successfully! Now you have... less nothing? Congrats?
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_8: Clicked 'done' on something that doesn't even exist. Is that philosophy or laziness? Both?
cat_emptyTaskDeleted_9: You really managed to make nothing happen. That's... an achievement, I guess?
